~A Greek philosopher was having a conversation with Zeus.`  He asked Zeus, "what's a million years to you?"`  Zeus said:  "a second."`  Then the man asked, "well, what's a million gold pieces to you?"`  And Zeus replied, "a copper penny."`  The man then asked, "Zeus, can you spare a copper penny for me?"`  Zeus said, "Yes I can son...in a second."`

~The range of visible light that we as humans can see is very small in relation to the entire spectrum.`  The light that we can see is:  red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo and violet (just remember the name ROY G. BIV).`  These are also the colors you see in a rainbow.`

~There are 50 states in the United States of America.`  In 1959 Hawaii and Alaska were admitted to the Union as the 49th and 50th states.`  California became a state in 1850.`  The capital of California is Sacramento.`  It is the third largest state in the union behind Alaska and Texas.`  The smallest state in the nation is Rhode Island.`  Florida is a popular vacation state whose capital is Tallahassee.`  New York was one of the original 13 states.`  New York City is divided into five boroughs:  the Bronx, Brooklyn, Manhattan, Queens and Richmond.`  The capital of New York is Albany.`

~In Hawaii there are eight major islands: Hawaii, Maui, Oahu, Kauai, Molokai, Lanai, Niihau, Kahoolawe.`  Although Hawaii is considered paradise by many of its visitors as well as its inhabitants, even in paradise it rains.`  Hawaii is one of the wettest states in the country in terms of rainfall where rain falls approximately 30% of the time.`  Honolulu is the capital of Hawaii.`  The state of Wyoming (Cheyenne is the capital.) was admitted to the Union in 1890.`  It is a state of wide open spaces and plenty of mosquitoes.`  It is 97,914 sq mi. and has a sparse population of 500,000.`

